1
00:00:18,510 --> 00:00:28,670
All that had been going on, I just, Robin and I had had it with information and terror and blood and just date night. We needed to get out.

2
00:00:29,290 --> 00:00:37,730
We take a Friday night anyway, but it was very important that we make sure we got out this Friday night and we had dinner just downtown here and just enjoyed each other.

3
00:00:37,730 --> 00:00:41,630
And we knew that there was a Christian concert taking place here at our church.

4
00:00:41,630 --> 00:00:47,610
and we dared to venture feeling rather old at our ripe old age of late 30s

5
00:00:47,610 --> 00:00:51,070
and we walked into our own sanctuary over here

6
00:00:51,070 --> 00:00:55,060
and it took me back a long time.

7
00:00:56,360 --> 00:01:00,220
And here was a band that had been brought in from southern Indiana called The Elms

8
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:01,740
and I was skeptical.

9
00:01:02,060 --> 00:01:03,860
I thought, okay, it's going to be a punk rock show

10
00:01:03,860 --> 00:01:05,240
and I'm not going to understand anything

11
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:07,800
and it's just going to be way outside of my boundaries.

12
00:01:08,580 --> 00:01:12,240
Come to find out, it was a real blessing.

13
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:15,260
We were blessed that night by this band,

14
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:17,020
these young guys from southern Indiana.

15
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:23,320
The connection is Robbins, my wife's sister,

16
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:26,850
is married to a gentleman whose brother,

17
00:01:27,930 --> 00:01:28,630
did you catch that?

18
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:30,110
Okay.

19
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:32,590
Robbins' sister's husband's brother

20
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:37,090
is the premier Christian rock promoter in Orange County.

21
00:01:37,570 --> 00:01:41,260
We have, according to Tim Tabor,

22
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:45,870
the best concert venue anywhere in Orange County.

23
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:47,640
Praise the Lord.

24
00:01:48,670 --> 00:01:50,850
So we have these bands being brought in.

25
00:01:50,930 --> 00:01:55,590
All we do is flip on the lights and say, have a great time, and we show up and get blessed,

26
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:58,700
and they do everything, and we get exposure.

27
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:02,380
There were over 100 kids from all over Orange County, even out to San Bernardino, coming

28
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:07,460
and just having a worship, jumping around in Jesus kind of experience.

29
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:17,160
And as I stood in the back, feeling old, you understand, but I remembered myself at 14,

30
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:22,420
at 18, at 22, 24, going to shows like that

31
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:25,260
and having the Lord minister to me through those events

32
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:27,600
and how those were part of my journey

33
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:33,060
in staying close to Jesus through my teens and early 20s.

34
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,440
And I was so proud of us to have a place

35
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,420
where that kind of event could take place

36
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:43,220
with an excellence and a quality that I never got to experience.

37
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:45,520
And I was proud to share that.

38
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,280
And they said, hey, you've got the best venue around.

39
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,120
We're coming back.

40
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,360
We're going to sling through a whole bunch of shows here.

41
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,900
And there will be kids coming from all over the place.

42
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:57,080
I just want to share that, that in the midst of tough times,

43
00:02:57,140 --> 00:02:58,980
there's good things happening in ministry.

44
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,820
And then after that whole thing was over, Saturday morning,

45
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:05,140
we turned that place into a basketball venue all over again.

46
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:08,380
That's what that was designed for, multiple use.

47
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:12,350
And all these families hearing about Jesus Saturday morning with basketball.

48
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:14,050
It was just a wonderful weekend.

49
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,350
So amidst our challenges, God is still on the throne.

50
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:18,630
God is still doing ministry.

51
00:03:18,810 --> 00:03:21,170
God is still bringing people to himself.

52
00:03:21,730 --> 00:03:25,250
And we're going to stay faithful in the midst of all that's happening.

53
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,160
Well, with that, I encourage you to journey with me a little bit.

54
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:36,300
Imagine, if you will, an early morning as the sun is beginning to brighten the sky.

55
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:40,760
A man moves silently through a vineyard.

56
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:43,030
He's got work to do.

57
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:51,270
And as he does it with determination and precision, he pauses to sharpen a pruning knife.

58
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:54,990
He gets the blade very, very crisp and ready to go.

59
00:03:55,470 --> 00:04:01,050
Because he knows that he will be most effective when his knife is very sharp.

60
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:10,730
And he works with skill, reaching here and then there and slashing a loose branch from the vine.

61
00:04:10,730 --> 00:04:15,030
occasionally even slicing into a whole bunch of grapes

62
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,790
and letting them fall to the ground.

63
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:20,710
And when he's finished with that vine,

64
00:04:20,830 --> 00:04:24,570
he moves on, leaving a stump where a branch had been

65
00:04:24,570 --> 00:04:28,310
with the sap kind of oozing in the early glistening sunlight.

66
00:04:30,860 --> 00:04:34,020
The vine dresser moves from vine to vine.

67
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,040
That's the imagery.

68
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,460
That's the kind of mental picture

69
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:43,460
that Jesus is using in his last discourse

70
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:45,460
and challenge to his disciples.

71
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:49,910
Jesus is giving his disciples his final thoughts,

72
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:52,610
giving them his final marching orders.

73
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:54,750
And as Eric pointed out last week,

74
00:04:55,030 --> 00:04:57,230
the mission is to be continued.

75
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:01,730
And here's how they are to do it.

76
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:06,210
From John chapter 15,

77
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:08,640
Jesus says,

78
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,920
I am the true vine,

79
00:05:11,590 --> 00:05:14,230
and my Father is the gardener.

80
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:19,160
He cuts off every branch that doesn't produce fruit

81
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:25,020
and he prunes the branches that do bear fruit so that even more fruit will be produced.

82
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:32,200
You have already been pruned for greater fruitfulness by the message I have given you.

83
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:36,360
Remain in me and I will remain in you.

84
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:40,980
For a branch cannot produce fruit if it is severed from the vine

85
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:44,380
and you cannot be fruitful apart from me.

86
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:49,830
Yes, I am the vine, you are the branches.

87
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:54,790
Those who remain in me and I in them will produce much fruit.

88
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,960
For apart from me you can do nothing.

89
00:05:59,370 --> 00:06:04,830
Anyone who parts from me is thrown away like a useless branch and withers.

90
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:08,810
Such branches are gathered into a pile to be burned.

91
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:14,000
But if you stay joined to me and my words remain in you,

92
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:18,700
you may ask any request you like and it will be granted.

93
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:25,700
My true disciples produce much fruit, and this brings great glory to my Father.

94
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:29,880
I have loved you even as the Father has loved me.

95
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:31,600
Remain in my love.

96
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:39,510
When you obey me, you remain in my love, just as I obey my Father and remain in his love.

97
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:44,020
I have told you this so that you will be filled with my joy.

98
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,580
Yes, your joy will overflow.

99
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:52,100
Lo, I command you to love each other in the same way that I love you.

100
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,520
And here is how to measure it.

101
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:59,060
The greatest love is shown when people lay their lives down for their friends.

102
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:03,440
You are my friends if you obey me.

103
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:09,550
I no longer call you servants, but a master doesn't confide in his servants.

104
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,590
Now you are my friends.

105
00:07:11,590 --> 00:07:19,090
Since I have told you everything the Father has told me, you didn't choose me, I chose you.

106
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:24,260
I appointed you to go and produce fruit that will last.

107
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:28,480
So the Father will give you whatever you ask for using my name.

108
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:32,360
I command you to love each other.

109
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:41,380
Friends, in times such as these, with the events of the world weighing heavily upon our hearts,

110
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:50,060
upon our heads the church must the church must rise up and carry on its mission without fear

111
00:07:50,060 --> 00:08:04,060
and with single-minded focus people need the lord people need the lord we are christ's ambassadors

112
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:10,880
we are the representatives of jesus christ on earth to spread this message to bring hope

113
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:15,580
especially in the midst of the challenges that face our world.

114
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:22,400
Jesus uses this image of a vine and branches to speak to the disciples.

115
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:28,470
Jesus wants the disciples to branch out, to branch out.

116
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:33,000
He wants the mission fulfilled in the world.

117
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:39,380
And so he gives four secrets to the disciples for how we are to bring about this mission,

118
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,700
how we are to branch out.

119
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:49,160
And the first one is this, the pruning by the Father.

120
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,670
Pruning by the Father.

121
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:57,870
As I've shared before, I don't have much experience with horticulture.

122
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:03,120
I don't know much about how to trim or prune or nurture a plant.

123
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:09,780
I'm kind of a throw some weed and feed on the lawn and watered a lot kind of gardener.

124
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,320
You know what I'm talking about?

125
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:15,010
Just spread it around and pray to God it lives.

126
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:16,940
That's my approach.

127
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:23,510
But my wife, bless her heart, she has good skills for plant care.

128
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:24,730
She has an eye.

129
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:28,490
She has the skill to take care of the plants, so I trust her.

130
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:32,960
Some of you think I'm just bowing out because I don't want to be responsible.

131
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,220
The fact is, I just kill plants.

132
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,680
This is a stewardship issue in our home.

133
00:09:41,650 --> 00:09:43,970
She doesn't want me touching the plants.

134
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:50,960
So Robin, with her clippers and other accoutrements, gets out there

135
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:54,520
and does violence to the plants.

136
00:09:55,810 --> 00:10:00,340
In my eye, bam, bam, bam, snip, snip, pieces are flying everywhere.

137
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:04,560
Death and destruction follows her pruning shears,

138
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:07,340
and I get to sweep it up.

139
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:08,900
That's how that works.

140
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:13,650
But you know what's amazing is she knows what she's doing,

141
00:10:13,730 --> 00:10:16,150
and after all this seeming violence to the plants,

142
00:10:16,430 --> 00:10:19,370
a few weeks later, there's new buds, there's new life,

143
00:10:19,370 --> 00:10:23,270
and there's new fullness coming in those plants.

144
00:10:24,530 --> 00:10:25,770
It's an amazing science.

145
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:31,950
I don't know how it works, but I know that even when you clip it back and the sap is oozing

146
00:10:31,950 --> 00:10:39,090
and it looks like the plant is crying in pain, it's good for it.

147
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:42,870
And it grows healthier and fuller and bigger.

148
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:48,080
And so Jesus uses that image of the vine dresser.

149
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:51,640
And Jesus is saying, he is the true vine.

150
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,180
It's no longer Israel.

151
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,000
Jesus is the true vine.

152
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,420
Jesus is God's planting.

153
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:04,830
And in that vineyard, there's pruning.

154
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:07,130
There's pruning.

155
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:12,190
Because the Father wants us to produce fruit.

156
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:16,520
What kind of fruit are we to produce?

157
00:11:17,730 --> 00:11:18,610
What's the mission?

158
00:11:19,930 --> 00:11:23,590
As Jesus is talking to the disciples, he's saying that he's going to leave them soon,

159
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:27,870
that the Holy Spirit is coming to empower them, and the mission is to carry on.

160
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:32,810
And the fruit that the disciples are to produce are things like worship,

161
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:42,230
and ministry, community, forming their spirits to be like Jesus, to outreach.

162
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:48,600
Jesus wants his followers to be the kind of people who love God and worship freely,

163
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,700
who love others in practical ways,

164
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:55,260
who experience real authentic community within the church,

165
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:59,480
who discipline their minds and their actions to conform to Jesus

166
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:05,570
and who share with others the hope that is found in Christ.

167
00:12:08,650 --> 00:12:09,590
That's what he wants.

168
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:14,380
He wants the fruit of the Spirit in our lives,

169
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:19,050
love and joy and peace and patience

170
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:21,880
and kindness and goodness

171
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:24,600
and faithfulness and gentleness

172
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,570
and self-control.

173
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:30,330
That's what a Christian is to look like.

174
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:34,060
And if we're going to be on Christ's mission in the world,

175
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:38,560
we have to be authentic, fruit-bearing disciples of Jesus Christ.

176
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:41,940
And for a vine to put out grapes,

177
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:48,920
There has to be that tending by that gardener, that slashing sometimes, that cutting, that pruning.

178
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,840
Friends, God does prune the branches sometimes.

179
00:12:56,480 --> 00:13:01,400
If we're the branches, if we are the branches, then God prunes the branches,

180
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:05,530
and that means He prunes us sometimes.

181
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:14,530
We all have various struggles in our lives, things that God needs to cut and to prune away.

182
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,920
Some of us struggle with our thoughts.

183
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:24,540
some with our attitudes, some with relationships,

184
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:29,970
some with various behaviors that don't honor God,

185
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:32,600
that have to be clipped and trimmed,

186
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:36,710
some with passion, some with service,

187
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,170
some with motives.

188
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:42,930
Our motives can get twisted, and it's time sometimes for the Lord

189
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:44,950
to come in and speak to us about our motives,

190
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:47,840
some with willingness.

191
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:51,260
God prunes the branches.

192
00:13:53,390 --> 00:13:54,390
How does He do that?

193
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,420
How does He prune us?

194
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:03,240
In verse 3 in that passage, it says that God prunes by Jesus' message.

195
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:07,190
And since Jesus' message is now embedded in the Scriptures,

196
00:14:08,090 --> 00:14:13,190
as we study and apply God's Word, allow it to course through our veins,

197
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:17,670
the Scriptures, as they speak to us, will prune us and challenge us.

198
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:26,520
God can prune through just the reading and the studying and the meditation and the application of His Word.

199
00:14:27,690 --> 00:14:30,030
The Bible also says in Hebrews chapter 12,

200
00:14:30,190 --> 00:14:34,450
God's discipline is always right and good for us

201
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:37,390
because it means we will share in his holiness.

202
00:14:39,190 --> 00:14:41,590
But no discipline is enjoyable while it's happening.

203
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,040
It's painful.

204
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:47,600
But afterward, there will be a quiet harvest of right living

205
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,820
for those who are trained in this way.

206
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:54,760
Friends, God may prune us.

207
00:14:54,860 --> 00:14:56,160
He may move us.

208
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,580
He may have us change jobs.

209
00:14:59,580 --> 00:15:08,420
he may change our neighbors he may remove some old friends he may remove some old habits

210
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:17,210
he may remove our jobs our income whatever it is that distracts us from himself he might move us

211
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:25,280
out of our comfort zones he might even humble us like he did jonah bring us to somebody else i

212
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:30,880
don't know how he's going to do it but god at times can discipline his children as an act of

213
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:43,360
pruning. Why? That we might produce more fruit, to be fuller. It doesn't feel good. It can be painful.

214
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:51,080
When a branch gets pruned, the sap oozes. It can sometimes feel like that when God disciplines us.

215
00:15:51,180 --> 00:16:00,950
We're raw. We're irritated. We're kind of oozing. Ow, Lord. But the gift of pain can make us grow.

216
00:16:03,050 --> 00:16:04,270
The gift of pain makes us grow.

217
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:05,590
Pain motivates.

218
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:07,090
Pain can push us.

219
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:11,300
Pain is often a pathway to growth.

220
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,000
And God wants us to be fruitful disciples.

221
00:16:17,390 --> 00:16:22,030
Sometimes he cuts back out of our lives the thing that holds us back from being fruitful.

222
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,760
So friends, if we're going to be effective in the mission,

223
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:30,560
sometimes we have to allow God to step into our lives and prune us back a bit

224
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:35,260
and shape some things in our lives that we might actually be fruitful for his kingdom.

225
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:39,800
And I don't know what that looks like in individual lives in this room.

226
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:44,760
I'm just asking you to be open that when God moves, and sometimes it hurts,

227
00:16:46,330 --> 00:16:48,210
to say, Father, I want to be fruitful.

228
00:16:49,430 --> 00:16:50,070
Have your way.

229
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:54,960
And don't try and resist His loving discipline.

230
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,720
For if the grapes were to move out of the way,

231
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:04,840
if the vine could wiggle out from under the movement of the vine dresser,

232
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,220
it would not ultimately be a healthy vine.

233
00:17:07,220 --> 00:17:18,760
Number two, the second secret for effective mission that Jesus is challenging us in this day is to remain in the sun.

234
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:24,560
Jesus said, I am the vine, you are the branches.

235
00:17:25,620 --> 00:17:30,220
Those who remain in me and I in them will produce much fruit.

236
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,380
For apart from me you can do nothing.

237
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:39,840
Thinking about vines and branches this week,

238
00:17:41,010 --> 00:17:43,470
I discovered, some of you may have been to this place,

239
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:48,270
that there is a vine, the oldest living vine, they think, in London,

240
00:17:48,890 --> 00:17:50,350
in a place called Hampton Court.

